Cell.Data: U.S. Office of the National Coordinator (ONC)
Defines how ValueSet is used to reflect code lists found in data element defintiions and form definitions to be used within the ONC's Structured Data Capture standard.
An additional title by which the questionnaire is known or should be represented, including what type of additional title it is.
Some questionnaires may have differing titles for display to patients than they do for display to researchers or clinicians. This extension allows capturing those other than for the patient.
Categorizes the type of alternate title. E.g. "Formal", "Scientific", "Previously Known as"
An additional description explaining the appropriate use of the questionnaire, including what type of additional description it is.
Some questionnaires may have differing descriptions for display to patients than they do for display to researchers or clinicians. This extension allows capturing those other than for the patient.
Categorizes the type of additional questionnaire description. E.g. "Formal", "Scientific"
Provides rules governing the use of this questionnaire from a privacy and/or security perspective. E.g. "confidential when completed"
Omission of this extensions doesn't indicate a lack of security or privacy considerations. They may be reflected in the description or might be implicit in context or workflow.
The base URL for the server to which questionnaire answers associated with this questionnaire should be submitted

Indicates that the form has been designed with an expectation that it will be submitted to the specified URI. If multiple endpoints are specified, expectation is that answers are submitted to all endpoints
If specified, indicates that the group should be rendered as a repeating header or footer on each "page" of the questionnaire.
When omitted, sections are presumed to be "regular" sections.
Extra text to display for group
Additional text to display at the group level along with guidance as to what sort of text it is.
Allows capturing tool tips, help text, text to display following a group, etc.
Categorizes the type of additional group text. E.g. "Tool tip", "Help", "Trailing text", etc.
The type of text may provide guidance for how/when to display the information.
Extra text to display for question
Additional text to display for the question along with guidance as to what sort of text it is.
Allows capturing tool tips, help text, text to display following a group, units, etc.
Categorizes the type of additional group text. E.g. "Tool tip", "Help", "Trailing text", "Units" etc.
The type of text may provide guidance for how/when to display the information.
